# Documentation workflow

Paths assume this scaffold was installed at the **repo root** as `.cursor/`
and the spec pack lives in `docs/`.

## At session start

When the user asks to implement, continue, or review work:

1. Read `docs/STATUS.md` and `docs/TASKS.md`
2. Read files under `docs/spec/` only if the task needs requirements
3. Read `docs/idea.md` / `docs/architecture.md` if scope or boundaries are unclear
4. Read `docs/hwfi-reference.md` before copying behaviour from the hwfi repo

## During implementation

- Code and tests are the source of truth for behaviour
- Do not update docs after every file edit
- Use session todos for in-chat progress; use `docs/TASKS.md` for durable backlog
- Prefer adding stdlib *in* the language over new host builtins when possible

## Before finishing meaningful work

1. Rewrite `docs/STATUS.md` (keep under 80 lines)
2. Update `docs/TASKS.md` (active items only; archive done work)
3. Append to `docs/log/YYYY-MM.md` only for decisions, blockers resolved, or milestones

## Do not

- Log user prompts verbatim
- Duplicate git history in log files
- Leave long lists of completed tasks in `TASKS.md` — archive to
  `docs/log/archive/tasks-YYYY-MM.md`
- Reintroduce a step-DSL alongside the ML kernel
